Example
Scroll the document by 100px horizontally:

Copy
window.scrollBy(100, 0); // Scroll 100px to the right

Description
The scrollBy() method scrolls the document by the specified number of pixels.

For this method to work, the visible property of the window's scrollbar must be set to true!

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
scrollBy()	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
window.scrollBy(x_num, y_num)
Parameter Values
Parameter
Type
Description
x_num



Number



Required.
How many pixels to scroll horizontally.
Positive values will scroll to the right,
while negative values will scroll to the left
y_num



Number



Required.
How many pixels to scroll vertically.
Positive values will scroll down,
while negative values scroll up
Return Value
No return value

More Examples
Scroll the document by 100px vertically:

Copy
window.scrollBy(0, 100); // Scroll 100px downwards

Example
Scroll the document horizontally and vertically:

Copy
<button onclick="scrollWin(0, 50)">Scroll down</button> 
<button onclick="scrollWin(0, -50)">Scroll up</button> 
<button onclick="scrollWin(100, 0)">Scroll right</button> 
<button onclick="scrollWin(-100, 0)">Scroll left</button> 
<script> 
function scrollWin(x, y) { 
    window.scrollBy(x, y); 
} 
</script>
